cyclone.name: NATE
cyclone.current_location: about 25 mi SSW of San Andres Island
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to move northwest across Nicaragua and Honduras, emerge over the north-western Caribbean, then track northward across the Gulf of Mexico toward the northern Gulf Coast before curving northeast over the southeastern United States.

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Warning in effect from Sandy Bay Sirpi, Nicaragua to Punta Castilla, Honduras
weather_observation.warning_coast: Same as watch area; no U.S. coast yet under warning
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Central America (Nicaragua/Honduras), later northern Gulf Coast from Louisiana eastward to Florida Panhandle and eventually the Southeast U.S.
weather_observation.wind: A brief period of breezy to locally gusty winds possible early next week as the remnant low passes, but sustained tropical-storm-force winds are unlikely.
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected for New Jersey because the system will be a weakening inland low when nearest.
weather_observation.rainfall: 1â€“3 inches of rain possible with locally higher pockets, which could cause minor urban or poor-drainage flooding.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Isolated river rises and minor flooding of low-lying terminals or access roads cannot be ruled out.
